## Typography

### Font Families

| Family | Use | Weights |
|--------|-----|---------|
| **Next Display Extended** (sans-serif) | Primary — headings, body, UI | Light, Regular, Book, Medium, Bold, Extrabold |
| **Next Display** (sans-serif) | Condensed variant | Light, Regular, Book, Medium, Bold, Extrabold |
| **Next Serif** | Headlines, editorial | Light, Book, Regular, Medium, Bold |

All fonts available in OTF, TTF, WOFF, and WOFF2 (Drive: BrandIdentity/Fonts).

### Type Hierarchy

| Style | Font | Tracking | Line Height |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| Large Heading | Next Display Extended **Bold** | 5% | 100% |
| Large Heading Alt | Next Display Extended **Medium** | 2% | 100% |
| Medium Heading | Next Display Extended **Bold** | 10% | 100% |
| Medium Heading Alt | Next Display Extended **Regular** | 0% | 150% |
| Small Heading | Next Display Extended **Medium** | 10% | 150% |
| Paragraph | Next Display Extended **Regular** | 0% | 150% |
| Small Paragraph | Next Display Extended **Regular** | 0% | 150% |

### Type Rules

- **Uppercase headings** are standard.
- Lowercase headings only for conversational/softer messaging, in very small amounts.
- Scale typography in **140% increments** for consistent spacing.
- Within a sentence, go up or down **one weight** for emphasis hierarchy.

